  "prompt": "When is the CA-CPT exam held?",
  "response": "The **CA-CPT (Common Proficiency Test)**, now known as the **CA Foundation Course**, is typically conducted **twice a year**. The examination sessions are usually scheduled in:\n\n1. **May Session:** Typically held in the month of **May**.\n2. **November Session:** Typically held in the month of **November**.\n\n**Key Points:**\n\n- **Exam Frequency:** Twice annually (May and November).\n- **Conducting Body:** Institute of Chartered Accountants of India (ICAI).\n- **Registration:** It's essential to keep an eye on the **official ICAI website** ([www.icai.org](https://www.icai.org)) for the latest updates on examination dates, registration deadlines, and any changes to the schedule.\n- **Preparation:** Ensure you refer to the latest syllabus and study materials provided by ICAI to prepare effectively for the exam.\n\n**Upcoming Exam Dates:**\nAs of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, specific dates for upcoming sessions may not have been announced yet. I recommend regularly checking the [ICAI's official notifications page](https://www.icai.org/post.html?post_id=8984) or contacting ICAI directly for the most accurate and up-to-date information.\n\n**Additional Tips:**\n\n- **Registration:** Start the registration process early to avoid last-minute issues.\n- **Eligibility:** Ensure you meet all the eligibility criteria outlined by ICAI before applying.\n- **Resources:** Utilize ICAI-provided study materials, mock tests, and coaching classes if necessary to enhance your preparation.\n\nIf you have any further questions or need assistance with specific aspects of the CA-CPT/CA Foundation exam, feel free to ask!",
